BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Search Innovations with OpenSearch
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/Berlin:20260502T161500
DTEND;TZID=Europe/Berlin:20260502T170000
DESCRIPTION:In this talk I will present the Innovations in Search with Ope
 nSearch\, a completely open-source search engine. The OpenSearch project c
 omes under Linux Foundation. \n\nI will dive into differentiating capabili
 ties like scalable Neural Sparse ANN Search using the SEISMIC algorithm\, 
 and the new Search Relevance Workbench for metric-driven relevance evaluat
 ion. Discover how system-generated Search Pipelines eliminate configuratio
 n overhead\, automatically building Vector Search pipelines at query runti
 me and UI editor for AI Search workflow set up.\n\nThe talk will include a
  demo on \n1/ Agentic Search with OpenSearch using locally hosted LLM mode
 ls\n2/ Search Relevance Workbench to improve Search Relevance and lastly \
 n3/ a preview of the upcoming Agentic Search Relevance Tuning that makes t
 uning Relevance easier\n\nhttps://luga.de/static/LIT-2026/talks/search_inn
 ovations_with_opensearch/
LOCATION:Raum C\; Technische Hochschule Augsburg\, Fakultät für Informat
 ik\, Friedberger Straße 2
ORGANIZER;CN="LUGA (Linux User Group Augsburg)":MAILTO:lit-2026@luga.de
BEGIN:VALARM
ACTION:DISPLAY
DESCRIPTION:Veranstaltung in 15 Minuten
TRIGGER:-PT15M
END:VALARM
END:VEVENT
END:VCALENDAR
